Context System (Agent Context)

One of the key things I learned was how to use agent context.

I created a context that stores available products.

@dataclass
class StoreContext:
    products: List[Product]

Then I initialized it with sample data.

context = StoreContext(
    products=[
        Product("Laptop", 1000),
        Product("Mouse", 25),
        Product("Keyboard", 75),
    ]
)
Why I used this

The context allows the agent and tools to access shared application data.

In this project, the context stores the product catalog.

5. Function Tools

A major concept I explored was function tools.

Tools allow the agent to call Python functions when needed.

I used the @function_tool decorator.

Tool: List Products
@function_tool
async def list_products(wrapper: RunContextWrapper[StoreContext]) -> str:

This tool returns all products in the store.

Tool: Calculate Total Price
@function_tool
async def calculate_total(wrapper: RunContextWrapper[StoreContext], product_name: str, quantity: int) -> str:

This tool calculates the total cost of a product based on quantity.

Tool: Recommend Product
@function_tool
async def recommend_product(wrapper: RunContextWrapper[StoreContext]) -> str:

This tool recommends the cheapest product.

6. RunContextWrapper

Each tool receives a wrapper object.

RunContextWrapper[StoreContext]
Why I used this

This wrapper gives tools access to the shared context data.

Example:

wrapper.context.products

This allows tools to access the product list.